The paper deals with visual recognition tasks using Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs), which are commonly used in computer vision and image processing. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also investigates the internal representation of CNNs and their association with semantic parts, which falls under the scope of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper uses quantitative analyses and human judgements, which could be relevant to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
